The National Chairman of the National Action Council (NAC), Dr. Olapade Agoro, yesterday, in Ibadan, declared intention to lead his political party to contest the 2019 presidential election. He said both the ruling APC and PDP have failed Nigerians. Agoro who declared his ambition during a meeting with leaders of the party across the country, said he decided to join the race with a 21-point agenda to address series of socio-economic and political problems militating development in Nigeria. He promised to ensure the principle of true federalism with each state being allowed to develop at her own pace, even as he said the oneness and unity of Nigeria would remain sacrosanct.